cs.IT, cs.NI, cs.SY, cs.MM, cs.AR 

Reasoning: 
1. cs.IT (Information Theory): The paper discusses the implementation and application possibilities of a compact full duplex MIMO architecture, which involves information theory concepts such as self-interference cancelation and channel capacity. 
2. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture): The paper focuses on the design and implementation of a full duplex MIMO physical layer for device-to-device (D2D) and cellular link coexisting on the same spectrum. 
3. cs.SY (Systems and Control): The paper proposes a novel timing synchronization method to construct a more viable full duplex MIMO link, which involves system design and control. 
4. cs.MM (Multimedia): The paper discusses the performance characterization of the proposed compact full duplex MIMO system, which involves multimedia applications such as video streaming and voice communication. 
5. cs.AR (Hardware Architecture): The paper implements the full duplex MIMO physical layer on an FPGA-based software-defined radio platform, which involves hardware architecture and design.
